This paper is about annotating materials synthesis procedures with structured representations, which involves natural language processing and information extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses challenges in annotating scientific text, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of automated synthesis planning, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
